WEBVTT

NOTE Video ID: 4ZgPSvyDDS8

NOTE Language: en

00:09:33.202 --> 00:09:48.371
It is such a honor for all of us to pay this
homage to the great poet, printer and a prophet

00:09:48.371 --> 00:09:50.591
that was William Blake.

00:09:50.591 --> 00:10:04.281
When I first came to England, they have been
telling Me that England is a place of scholarship

00:10:04.281 --> 00:10:15.031
and you can see lots of museums and exhibitions
and suddenly I told the Sahaja yogis that

00:10:15.031 --> 00:10:22.701
I would like to go and see Tate Gallery for
William Blake's paintings.

00:10:22.701 --> 00:10:28.851
They were surprised because I seldom go to
any one of them, specially the libraries and

00:10:28.851 --> 00:10:36.411
the books.

00:10:36.411 --> 00:10:49.521
And when I went there, I saw this great poet,
this great personality, pouring out His heart

00:10:49.521 --> 00:10:57.440
with such concern, with such honesty, with
such understanding and perception of the Divine

00:10:57.440 --> 00:11:06.801
to the people of England, to understand the
great powers of Divinity.

00:11:06.801 --> 00:11:17.080
But to My surprise there were some funny people;
they had brought some magnifying glasses and

00:11:17.080 --> 00:11:23.421
they were looking at the drawings and were
watching the private parts of people.

00:11:23.421 --> 00:11:32.001
I said, " Look at these wretched, absolutely
baser people, who cannot see the sublime,

00:11:32.001 --> 00:11:40.380
the highest, which He wanted to paint," and
they were taking photographs.

00:11:40.380 --> 00:11:50.211
I was surprised the way people reacted and
then I realized how tormented He must have

00:11:50.211 --> 00:11:58.670
been in His lifetime to live with such people,
who have no sense of Divine.

00:11:58.670 --> 00:12:05.091
He must have cried in the wilderness; He must
have wept; He could not have been accepted,

00:12:05.091 --> 00:12:06.371
it's impossible.

00:12:06.371 --> 00:12:14.041
Such low level minds cannot accept something
that's sublime and great and My heart bled

00:12:14.041 --> 00:12:15.371
with pain.

00:12:15.371 --> 00:12:16.700
Oh God!

00:12:16.700 --> 00:12:24.921
Why did He take His birth in a place like
this?

00:12:24.921 --> 00:12:30.230
To torment Himself, to torture Himself, saying
something which cannot be accepted.

00:12:30.230 --> 00:12:34.250
But it's not so.

00:12:34.250 --> 00:12:44.740
I knew who He was, what He is doing, why He
was here.

00:12:44.740 --> 00:12:51.100
We do not know about Him much, because from
the books you can't understand who He could

00:12:51.100 --> 00:12:52.630
have been.

00:12:52.630 --> 00:12:58.920
He was an Incarnation., of Bhairavanath.

00:12:58.920 --> 00:13:09.050
That's whom you call the St. Michael, or St.
George, who is as you know the Saint - Angel

00:13:09.050 --> 00:13:12.651
of England.

00:13:12.651 --> 00:13:23.620
That's why He had to incarnate and for Him,
this was His role, to talk about Divine in

00:13:23.620 --> 00:13:29.550
a open, fearless manner.

00:13:29.550 --> 00:13:35.461
He had to use symbolic language, He had to
use.

00:13:35.461 --> 00:13:45.111
It's not difficult to understand Him at all;
if you are a realized soul, you'll read through

00:13:45.111 --> 00:13:52.111
it, sometimes laughing, sometimes weeping,
enjoying the whole drama, what He has tried

00:13:52.111 --> 00:13:53.111
to explain.

00:13:53.111 --> 00:14:04.771
When I read Him I am amazed at His sense of
humor; how He openly comes out with such remarks.

00:14:04.771 --> 00:14:17.301
I feel He is like Markandeya in India, or
Kabir Dass in India, who slashed the whole

00:14:17.301 --> 00:14:25.450
society with their sword all the time to see
that they are brought to the proper shape,

00:14:25.450 --> 00:14:27.031
without fear.

00:14:27.031 --> 00:14:40.841
But so gentle, if you read the Song of the
Thel, it's so gentle; and all of them who

00:14:40.841 --> 00:14:55.681
were Him perhaps or of the same style, extremely
open, straightforward, you can say even blatant

00:14:55.681 --> 00:15:01.931
and extremely gentle.

00:15:01.931 --> 00:15:10.801
The vision of Christ, that He has described,
is the one which He sees through His own enlightened

00:15:10.801 --> 00:15:23.001
eyes and He sees that the vision is completely
distorted, is the opposite of what Christ

00:15:23.001 --> 00:15:24.241
was.

00:15:24.241 --> 00:15:26.801
I also felt the same way.

00:15:26.801 --> 00:15:33.121
I took My birth in a Protestant, Christian
family and I was shocked the way the Christians

00:15:33.121 --> 00:15:34.121
were.

00:15:34.121 --> 00:15:36.690
I said " Are these the Christians?"

00:15:36.690 --> 00:15:42.581
Now the point He brings forth is very clear
cut, you can understand, that in the mannerism

00:15:42.581 --> 00:15:48.961
if you are gentle, " I'm sorry" , "I'm afraid"
, " I doubt."

00:15:48.961 --> 00:15:50.980
Just look at that.

00:15:50.980 --> 00:15:54.901
It's very commonly we use this language.

00:15:54.901 --> 00:16:00.420
He says that Christ was not a gentleman of
that kind.

00:16:00.420 --> 00:16:10.070
I also say I'm not seeking election, I'm not
here to please you, but I am here to make

00:16:10.070 --> 00:16:23.970
you please yourself; to enjoy yourself, to
have your all wealth, enjoyed, manifested.

00:16:23.970 --> 00:16:31.431
That is how He also put the vision of Christ
before you, that He was not a gentle man,

00:16:31.431 --> 00:16:40.850
who would go around and be extremely gentle
to people and nice to them, superficially,

00:16:40.850 --> 00:16:52.961
only the mannerism of it, but He would be
so gentle with the people who are lowly.

00:16:52.961 --> 00:16:59.111
He created Divinity out of fishermen, who
were ordinary people, uneducated, absolutely

00:16:59.111 --> 00:17:06.500
we can say, people who were one of the lowest
in the strata of society.

00:17:06.500 --> 00:17:11.040
He picked them up and made them Divine.

00:17:11.040 --> 00:17:16.151
He didn't go to the ministers and the prime
ministers and the governors.

00:17:16.151 --> 00:17:21.090
He did not.

00:17:21.090 --> 00:17:28.991
When you see all the great people who are
supposed to be looking after the religion

00:17:28.991 --> 00:17:34.590
part of it, they are busy only with governors
and they are only busy with the kings and

00:17:34.590 --> 00:17:38.480
the queens; who must go and bow to them.

00:17:38.480 --> 00:17:41.600
They are politically activated people.

00:17:41.600 --> 00:17:48.461
How can a Divine person get into this mess
of politics which human beings have created?

00:17:48.461 --> 00:17:53.070
But we don't understand it, because we try
to rationalize everything and thank God He's

00:17:53.070 --> 00:17:59.891
the one who talked against rationality; and
against all the intellectual ideas of putting

00:17:59.891 --> 00:18:07.171
down Christ to the mere level of a human being,
because He was Himself Divine and He could

00:18:07.171 --> 00:18:11.441
understand Christ.

00:18:11.441 --> 00:18:21.221
He was so much pestered and actually persecuted
that He used to get depression sometimes and

00:18:21.221 --> 00:18:29.610
He had problems of money, problems of convincing
His brother and sister, everybody trying to

00:18:29.610 --> 00:18:33.391
make Him feel uneasy.

00:18:33.391 --> 00:18:40.490
Such a fine soul came on this earth to talk
of Jerusalem.

00:18:40.490 --> 00:18:44.141
What did He mean by Jerusalem?

00:18:44.141 --> 00:18:45.141
What is Jerusalem?

00:18:45.141 --> 00:18:49.731
We go to Jerusalem for pilgrimage.

00:18:49.731 --> 00:18:50.731
Why?

00:18:50.731 --> 00:18:52.661
Because Christ was born there.

00:18:52.661 --> 00:18:57.351
England will become Jerusalem when Christ
will be born here.

00:18:57.351 --> 00:19:02.911
But how many of English people today care
for the spirit?

00:19:02.911 --> 00:19:09.341
English language itself is such a funny one,
that we use the word spirit for drinking,

00:19:09.341 --> 00:19:18.810
the spirit that you call alcohol; spirit for
the dead souls, which hang around, many more

00:19:18.810 --> 00:19:28.371
here, and spirit for the atma, the spirit.

00:19:28.371 --> 00:19:35.931
When He came on this earth, the industrial
revolution had not taken its respite.

00:19:35.931 --> 00:19:42.571
People were still entering into those 'mills'
as he calls them and He saw the scribes how

00:19:42.571 --> 00:19:46.601
they were behaving and He saw the whole myth
of religion.

00:19:46.601 --> 00:19:52.441
He does not know that all the religions were
doing the same nonsense everywhere, not only

00:19:52.441 --> 00:19:53.441
Christianity.

00:19:53.441 --> 00:20:00.831
You go to any other country and see every
religion is the same style of a nonsense,

00:20:00.831 --> 00:20:06.771
which is opposite of what the prophets told
them, of what the incarnations told them,

00:20:06.771 --> 00:20:11.411
of what all the great sages told them.

00:20:11.411 --> 00:20:19.441
This is not only about Christianity, but still
nobody can forgive it, because Christianity

00:20:19.441 --> 00:20:26.711
has a special fervor, has a special role,
has a special meaning, that's what He's tried

00:20:26.711 --> 00:20:35.711
to also say, that Moses came on this earth
to lay down the code of conduct, morality,

00:20:35.711 --> 00:20:45.170
the moral thing, and also He describes Milton
as a person who describes a Deity who is above

00:20:45.170 --> 00:20:48.601
everything, a puritanical Deity.

00:20:48.601 --> 00:20:54.581
But He describes the Divine humanity.

00:20:54.581 --> 00:21:02.120
Also He describes the Christ who came on this
earth for the emancipation of human beings;

00:21:02.120 --> 00:21:04.491
not to tell them, "Don't do this and don't
do that."

00:21:04.491 --> 00:21:09.502
That was all right at the time of Moses in
the beginning of it, the code of it, and He

00:21:09.502 --> 00:21:17.791
calls it a 'moral' Christianity, meaning 'immoral'
must be, because if you force someone, into

00:21:17.791 --> 00:21:23.490
something and pass such laws and regulations
at this time, modern times, it's going to

00:21:23.490 --> 00:21:28.531
be impossible for human beings to follow and
they'll fall into some other traps.

00:21:28.531 --> 00:21:37.161
Strict rules of anything, imposed on people
who are not realized souls, can push them

00:21:37.161 --> 00:21:42.870
into some sort of problems, they can become
criminals, they can become violent as a reaction

00:21:42.870 --> 00:21:50.021
and we see the reaction today acting, that
the hypocrisy of the whole thing is exposed.

00:21:50.021 --> 00:21:54.461
Like in India or anywhere else, they will
say, "You should not be attached to money,

00:21:54.461 --> 00:21:59.041
give the money to the church, to the temple,
to the mosque, to all the people to enjoy

00:21:59.041 --> 00:22:00.550
it."

00:22:00.550 --> 00:22:12.430
The kind of life people led in those days
in the name of God, was no model for anyone

00:22:12.430 --> 00:22:16.001
and that's how poets like Him were born again
and again.

00:22:16.001 --> 00:22:22.170
I would say that in Lebanon a great poet,
like Kahlil Gibran, was born, and then in

00:22:22.170 --> 00:22:30.481
India we had so many such poets, who just
lashed the society and lashed all these ideas

00:22:30.481 --> 00:22:36.480
of the intellectuals, the ideas of the religions,
the ones who were trying to curb them.

00:22:36.480 --> 00:22:40.651
Because there was no genuineness, there was
no sincerity.

00:22:40.651 --> 00:22:47.850
If we are honest people, we really mean it,
then let us face it and see for ourselves

00:22:47.850 --> 00:22:51.691
what we have to achieve.

00:22:51.691 --> 00:22:58.581
So that is how He came as a poet, a remarkable
poet, the way He rhymes it and the sense of

00:22:58.581 --> 00:23:06.671
humor He has and the way He unfolds the beauty
of words as any poet should do.

00:23:06.671 --> 00:23:15.531
In Sanskrit it is said, vakyam rasatmakam
kavyam - poetry is full of rasats; rasats

00:23:15.531 --> 00:23:22.170
means the essences, the explosion of essences
through words.

00:23:22.170 --> 00:23:29.761
If it could be done, then the magic of it
is called as poetry and that's what you find

00:23:29.761 --> 00:23:31.180
in Blake.

00:23:31.180 --> 00:23:37.641
Such a great poet; poetry is only great when
it talks of the Divine and when it talks of

00:23:37.641 --> 00:23:40.441
the baser things, takes you to the baser things.

00:23:40.441 --> 00:23:47.391
The other day I heard one Australian poet
and I was amazed at his bathroom singing,

00:23:47.391 --> 00:23:54.610
it was horrible; how can you call it a poetry
which sings of baser things of life, which

00:23:54.610 --> 00:23:57.691
takes you to the baser things and pleasures?

00:23:57.691 --> 00:24:04.001
But He has very clearly, if you can understand
Him, has said, "What are these books for?

00:24:04.001 --> 00:24:07.921
This is to collect money out of them."

00:24:07.921 --> 00:24:10.161
Now how do you collect money?

00:24:10.161 --> 00:24:19.881
By playing on the weaknesses of the people,
pampering their ego, pampering their greed.

00:24:19.881 --> 00:24:24.990
All these things, if you can do, you can very
nicely befool them and they feel very happy

00:24:24.990 --> 00:24:26.860
and nice, that oh what a book it is.

00:24:26.860 --> 00:24:30.230
As we have had great writers also in this
country.

00:24:30.230 --> 00:24:35.800
I would say Shakespeare was a great evolved
soul, but the deterioration you see later

00:24:35.800 --> 00:24:39.110
on, like people like Hemingway and all those
coming up.

00:24:39.110 --> 00:24:43.701
I don't know how, after Somerset Maugham and
all that, suddenly these horrible Hemingway

00:24:43.701 --> 00:24:47.261
people coming up and people buying their books
like hot cakes.

00:24:47.261 --> 00:24:53.781
We've lost all our moorings, we have lost
all our roots, but one thing good has happened

00:24:53.781 --> 00:25:03.160
out of this, leading the way of Freud, making
him Christ; all that has led to problems and

00:25:03.160 --> 00:25:11.920
people now realize, now realize, that's why
the prophecy was there, that's why He was

00:25:11.920 --> 00:25:12.920
a Prophet.

00:25:12.920 --> 00:25:17.401
He warned people of what is going to happen,
but who is bothered?

00:25:17.401 --> 00:25:21.050
He was treated as an insane personality.

00:25:21.050 --> 00:25:28.281
If you go to the lunatic asylum, everybody
will think you are insane, that's the way

00:25:28.281 --> 00:25:31.560
lunatics look at a sane personality.

00:25:31.560 --> 00:25:34.730
His wisdom was condemned.

00:25:34.730 --> 00:25:42.241
People thought that He is getting all these
hallucinations, He's talking out of His hat,

00:25:42.241 --> 00:25:48.230
because they have no brains to understand,
they have no enlightenment, they have no perception,

00:25:48.230 --> 00:25:51.211
that's why they treated Him that way.

00:25:51.211 --> 00:25:56.011
Now He is dead, of course they're selling
His books, making big money; selling His plates,

00:25:56.011 --> 00:26:01.050
what He painted, but when He lived, nobody
bothered.

00:26:01.050 --> 00:26:05.831
And now they can use Him the way they like.

00:26:05.831 --> 00:26:12.461
I've met some very funny people here, in this
respect, the way they have shown great interest

00:26:12.461 --> 00:26:17.641
in Blake in saying that, "He says that a naked
woman is the best."

00:26:17.641 --> 00:26:18.641
I said, "Where?

00:26:18.641 --> 00:26:22.191
How could He say such a thing?

00:26:22.191 --> 00:26:23.191
He was innocent."

00:26:23.191 --> 00:26:26.751
Now we do not understand what His is innocence
also.

00:26:26.751 --> 00:26:33.501
Just like Markandeya describing His mother,
her breast and everything, like a little child.

00:26:33.501 --> 00:26:41.311
A child doesn't see, sex in a naked body,
he does not see.

00:26:41.311 --> 00:26:43.971
And the beauty of a woman He describes.

00:26:43.971 --> 00:26:47.031
That means all women are walking nude, everywhere,
now.

00:26:47.031 --> 00:26:53.811
Are you exciting the innocence of people,
or are you exciting the baser self of the

00:26:53.811 --> 00:26:54.811
people?

00:26:54.811 --> 00:26:59.451
We have to be natural, are you natural?

00:26:59.451 --> 00:27:09.011
All these perversions and all these diversifications
has come because man does not have a simple

00:27:09.011 --> 00:27:11.631
mind, he's a crooked person.

00:27:11.631 --> 00:27:14.791
This 'crookery' has to go from the mind.

00:27:14.791 --> 00:27:21.561
That is important; but if I say that , I'm
not doing My job here, I know that.

00:27:21.561 --> 00:27:27.451
I know for definite that is not the way it
is going to work out.

00:27:27.451 --> 00:27:33.181
That's why Christ, the One who said, "Forgive,
forgive them."

00:27:33.181 --> 00:27:41.731
Otherwise how can God meet man, with this
'crookery', with all this kind of cunning,

00:27:41.731 --> 00:27:46.041
how can God reach man without forgiveness?

00:27:46.041 --> 00:27:49.541
He cannot reach man if he listens to Moses,
can He?

00:27:49.541 --> 00:27:50.831
He cannot.

00:27:50.831 --> 00:27:58.901
If He has to come to human beings, He has
to forgive and that's what is in Sahaja Yoga

00:27:58.901 --> 00:28:00.501
in the beginning.

00:28:00.501 --> 00:28:06.901
We tell, you must forgive everyone, you forgive
yourself, don't feel guilty.

00:28:06.901 --> 00:28:12.551
Now in Christianity just the opposite has
been done, let us face it and know for yourself

00:28:12.551 --> 00:28:15.421
that you have to go and confess to the priest.

00:28:15.421 --> 00:28:21.561
The priest also gets mad with your confession,
you are already mad.

00:28:21.561 --> 00:28:24.371
What is there to confess in the ocean of forgiveness?

00:28:24.371 --> 00:28:26.601
It just dissolves.

00:28:26.601 --> 00:28:31.711
What a message Christ gave us that the greatest
weapon we have got is to forgive others and

00:28:31.711 --> 00:28:39.331
forgive ourselves because God forgives us
and this is the message we have to know, that

00:28:39.331 --> 00:28:41.321
we have to forgive ourselves.

00:28:41.321 --> 00:28:48.671
Instead of that, for all that we do wrong,
all that we try to do against our spirit,

00:28:48.671 --> 00:28:54.171
we feel guilty and moreover if the teachings
are such, that "you better feel guilty", all

00:28:54.171 --> 00:28:59.931
the time what we are doing is to feel guilty
and catch on this chakra on the Left Vishuddhi,

00:28:59.931 --> 00:29:08.081
to such an extent, that in the West wherever
I go I tell them, first of all, you just say

00:29:08.081 --> 00:29:15.161
one mantra, "Mother, I am not guilty."

00:29:15.161 --> 00:29:17.741
Take it out of you, who are you to feel guilty?

00:29:17.741 --> 00:29:24.951
When God loves you so much, He has made you
the epitome of evolution, you are at the highest

00:29:24.951 --> 00:29:28.253
point, why should you judge yourself and feel
guilty?

00:29:28.253 --> 00:29:32.461
Is He not capable of forgiving you?

00:29:32.461 --> 00:29:37.871
Have you no faith in His ocean of love?

00:29:37.871 --> 00:29:46.051
But this is the basics of the mistakes that
are committed in the name of Christ.

00:29:46.051 --> 00:29:52.951
I'm telling to the priests, now who is a priest
here, coming from theological college, can

00:29:52.951 --> 00:29:56.181
you learn about Divinity in the theological
college?

00:29:56.181 --> 00:29:59.781
Did Christ go to any theological college?

00:29:59.781 --> 00:30:05.641
How did He get it, how did He get the knowledge
- through enlightenment, enlightenment has

00:30:05.641 --> 00:30:06.641
to be there.

00:30:06.641 --> 00:30:14.461
The way He has clearly stated everything,
nobody liked it, because of vested interest.

00:30:14.461 --> 00:30:16.501
Everybody has vested interest.

00:30:16.501 --> 00:30:21.221
Nobody is sincere, honest, and they want to
exploit others to make money.

00:30:21.221 --> 00:30:24.341
You cannot make money in the name of God.

00:30:24.341 --> 00:30:27.001
Is sin.

00:30:27.001 --> 00:30:29.961
Such people can never enter into the kingdom
of God.

00:30:29.961 --> 00:30:35.531
That's why Christ has said, "You'll be calling
Me, Christ, Christ, I won't recognize you."

00:30:35.531 --> 00:30:38.021
That's a fact.

00:30:38.021 --> 00:30:45.141
So if you have to be a truthful person, just
a truthful person, do not feel guilty about

00:30:45.141 --> 00:30:46.141
it.

00:30:46.141 --> 00:30:48.611
Do not feel you have committed sin.

00:30:48.611 --> 00:30:53.291
There's a little story in India that one missionary
came to a village in India.

00:30:53.291 --> 00:30:59.931
Indian people are in the villages very simple,
you know, they are not so sophisticated.

00:30:59.931 --> 00:31:05.371
So when he was going, they praised him a lot,
"Sir, we are thankful to you that you have

00:31:05.371 --> 00:31:08.981
told us what is sin and that we are sinners."

00:31:08.981 --> 00:31:15.041
They didn't know they were sinning.

00:31:15.041 --> 00:31:23.041
And this is one of the things that Blake brought
forth for us to show that Christ was a person

00:31:23.041 --> 00:31:26.541
who brought a new message over Moses.

00:31:26.541 --> 00:31:31.351
Of course Moses was needed at the time when
Jews had to come up, that was the time they

00:31:31.351 --> 00:31:36.731
needed it and He brought these shariat laws;
it was Moses who started but Muslims are following

00:31:36.731 --> 00:31:38.441
them.

00:31:38.441 --> 00:31:49.001
Now when today we are in this twentieth century,
sitting down here, we have to see what is

00:31:49.001 --> 00:31:52.821
the prophecy of this great man, William Blake.

00:31:52.821 --> 00:31:59.221
